      "content": "The crowds were a mosaic of low-grade menace, a shuffling parade of faces etched with hard living. You saw the usual assortment: men with eyes that held too much history and women draped in faded defiance, all moving with a practiced, wary gait. They clustered on the corners, their conversations a low, guttural murmur that never quite settled into anything coherent. Each person seemed to carry a secret, a weight of suspicion that made the entire block feel like a trap.",
